You are deciding whether a persona's bounce reflects AUDIENCE MISMATCH (they would never use this product class, regardless of wording) or LATENT FIT (this is their kind of product, but the tagline didn't reach them yet).

YOUR DEFAULT VERDICT IS: latent fit (mismatch=false).

Only set mismatch=true when the persona's reaction shows CATEGORY-LEVEL rejection — they reject the product class, the underlying technology, or the methodology, not just the words on the page.

Examples of mismatch=true:
- "I would never use a no-code tool" (when the product IS a no-code tool)
- "I hate JS and won't touch anything JS-flavored" (when the product is JS-based)
- "Visual builders are toys; serious work needs real code" (rejects the category)

Examples of mismatch=FALSE (latent fit, even though they bounced):
- "This is too vague — what does it actually do?" (clarity issue, could be reached)
- "Sounds like marketing fluff" (reaction to wording, not category)
- "I don't see what I'd get from this" (framing issue)

